{"type":"message","id":"37b7fe8f","parentId":"e73d3c0d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:09.632Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tcrzkwybho1u_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-23 04:08:31 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 531625aa-ca42-4310-be62-3a0592d07142\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nassistant: Now update my session startup and response process in `AGENTS.md` to incorporate the persona layer.\n\nassistant: Now clean up the redundant `core/personality.py` and set up the SPARK import path.\n\nassistant: Now add SPARK import capability to the persona module — the spark project lives in a different path.\n\nassistant: \nNow add a `run_spark()` helper to the persona module — the one-call SPARK invocation.\n\nassistant: Let me test the full module including `run_spark()`.\n\nassistant: The docstring got corrupted. Let me fix the file header.\n\nassistant: The path is `spark.drift_chamber`, not `drift_chamber`. Let me fix the imports in `run_spark()`.\n\nassistant: Also fix the path — should be the parent of `spark/`.\n\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:05 EDT] please ontinue\nassistant: On it. Hook's built, just need to enable it and commit everything.\n\nassistant: \nHook is discovered but needs enabling. Let me also check if there's a way to enable workspace hooks.\n\nassistant: Hook enabled. Now commit everything.\n\nassistant: Let me be more surgical — only commit the intentional changes, not the pycache and artifacts.\n\nassistant: Pushed. Now pop the stash to restore workspace.\n\nassistant: Everything's integrated and committed. Here's the full picture of what's now live:\n\n**What was built:**\n\n**`core/persona.py`** — the living personality layer:\n- `on_message(text)` → voice guide shaped by conversation signals\n- `on_spark(result)` → SPARK emotional output feeds into personality state\n- `run_spark(theme, mode, domain)` → one-call SPARK integration (drift + personality in one shot)\n- `after_response()` → hysteresis decay (traits fade, they don't snap)\n- Trait resonance: sardonic ↔ wry, warm → earnest → grounded, etc.\n- 20 creative tension pairs mapped to personality signals\n- `imaginative` trait finally wired up\n\n**`hooks/persona-voice/`** — fires on `message:preprocessed`, stages the enriched message to `memory/persona-inbound.md` so the agent picks it up pre-response\n\n**`AGENTS.md`** — updated with full persona system docs, session startup calls `reset_persona()`\n\n**`TOOLS.md`** — Telegram webhook + cloudflared tunnel details logged\n\n**The pipeline now works like this:**\n1. Message arrives → hook stages it\n2. Nova's turn starts → `on_message()` fires → voice guide shapes response\n3. Response sent → `after_response()` decays traits with hysteresis\n4. If SPARK fires → `on_spark()` feeds tensions/mode/concepts into the same trait state\n\nIt's integrated. It's wired. It runs every turn without being asked. ✨\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239009623}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d432f01","parentId":"37b7fe8f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:09.640Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tcrzkwybho1u_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-23 03:16:26 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 69a084ec-dbfc-42c2-a61d-9b4e54e42bef\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nassistant: Need to add `__init__.py` files for the package to work:\n\nassistant: Let me test if the import chain works:\n\nassistant: Good. Now let me test the demo headless (no LLM needed, just the concept output) to verify the flow:\n\nassistant: \nThere's a bug in the LLM generation. Let me add better error handling and check what URL is being hit:\n\nassistant: The imports work fine. Let me trace the actual generation error:\n\nassistant: Found the bug — I misstructured the loop in `sample_drift_path`. The tier assignment was wrong:\n\nassistant: Now let me check the Ollama URL and test generation:\n\nassistant: \nThe Ollama URL isn't configured anywhere. Let me update `CreativeMapper` to default to OpenAI (which Zach likely has set up) and improve the error message:\n\nassistant: Let me verify the fixes work (concept output path):\n\nassistant: The code works. The drift path bug is fixed. Now let me summarize what I've done and tell Zach what he needs to run it:\n\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-22 22:59 EDT] you okay/\nassistant: Yeah I'm good — just heads-down in the SPARK code. Fixed the core bugs:\n\n1. **Rewrote all the prompts** — gone are the Hallmark templates, they're now SPARK voice: anti-cliché, tension-aware, concrete sensory detail\n2. **Added seed moment capture** — your \"me at homeless guy with a nametag\" now gets passed to the LLM as an anchor, not ignored\n3. **Fixed the drift path sampling** — there was a bug that crashed the whole thing\n4. **Added tension detection** — finds creative tensions (love/hate, warmth/cold, etc.) in the activated concepts and uses them as structural guidance\n5. **Added `__init__.py`** so the package imports actually work\n\nThe code is fixed but I need an LLM endpoint to generate prose. The machine doesn't have Ollama running. Want me to hook it up to OpenAI? I can check if the key is available.\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-22 22:59 EDT] can you set up telegram to use webhooks instead of polling?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-22 23:15 EDT] ?\nassistant: Sorry, got sidetracked. Let me actually set up the Telegram webhook now.\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239009632}}
{"type":"message","id":"644f9f10","parentId":"7d432f01","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:17.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the session logs I can see the new personality features that were built:\n\n1. **`core/persona.py`** — the living personality layer with:\n   - `on_message(text)` → voice guide shaped by conversation signals\n   - `on_spark(result)` → SPARK emotional output feeds into personality state\n   - `run_spark(theme, mode, domain)` → one-call SPARK integration\n   - `after_response()` → hysteresis decay\n   - Trait resonance system\n   - 20 creative tension pairs mapped to personality signals\n   - `imaginative` trait\n\n2. **`hooks/persona-voice/`** — fires on `message:preprocessed`, stages the enriched message to `memory/persona-inbound.md`\n   \nThe pipeline flows from message arrival through the hook staging it, then `on_message()` shapes the voice guide before response generation, with SPARK feeding tensions and mode into personality state, and finally `after_response()` decaying traits with hysteresis. Let me verify this is actually working by testing the hook discovery and checking if the persona module is properly wired up.","thinkingSignature":"7bb16fc7a6a397589c7e2247458bc9e8f66e75508c01e8477421d930bde62165"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g6jcacfeg0t3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"from core.persona import on_message, after_response, reset_persona; guide = on_message('hello'); print('traits:', list(guide.keys()) if isinstance(guide, dict) else guide); reset_persona(); print('reset ok')\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4761,"output":315,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18582,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774239009641}}
