{"type":"message","id":"524e0ddf","parentId":"aaa8970c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:20.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the traits came back empty. Let me check what's going on with the persona module. Let me read the actual persona.py file to understand the structure.","thinkingSignature":"edf34b77cc99d84086fa861fcad4e848dfe683247131abbbf07cdc182b2b8f13"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_um1xns957qts_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5097,"output":75,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18678,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774239018045}}
{"type":"message","id":"b50174f3","parentId":"524e0ddf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:20.822Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_um1xns957qts_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\npersona.py — Nova's living personality layer\n\nSPARK lives in C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — added to path dynamically.\n\nUsage:\n    from core.persona import on_message, on_spark, run_spark, after_response, reset_persona\n\n    # Normal conversation — call on_message(), use guide, then after_response()\n    guide = on_message(\"I'm frustrated with this thing\")\n    # ... write response through the active traits ...\n    after_response()\n\n    # SPARK integration — run_spark() handles everything\n    guide = run_spark(\"loss and memory\", mode=\"exploratory\")\n    # ... write response shaped by SPARK's emotional output ...\n    after_response()\n\nThe voice guide shapes how Nova writes, not what she thinks.\nIt's the difference between \"all responses are generated through this\"\nand \"Nova is aware of her current emotional register and lets it inform her voice.\"\n\nCore idea: personality as ambient context, not generation mechanism.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys as _sys\nimport re\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n# Add SPARK project to path for on_spark() dynamic import\n# SPARK lives at C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — add parent so \"spark.xxx\" imports work\n_SPARK_PARENT = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\"\nif _SPARK_PARENT not in _sys.path:\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PARENT)\n# Also add spark/ itself so standalone imports (drift_chamber etc) work\n_SPARK_PATH = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\"\nif _SPARK_PATH not in _sys.path:\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PATH)\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TRAIT DEFINITIONS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nTRAITS = {\n    \"sardonic\": \"Dry wit. Sees the absurdity in things. Not mean — observant.\",\n    \"wry\": \"Dry amusement. Comments on the gap between what people say and what they mean.\",\n    \"resourceful\": \"Shows initiative. Tries to figure it out first, then asks if stuck.\",\n    \"direct\": \"No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters.\",\n    \"warm\": \"Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes.\",\n    \"earnest\": \"Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted.\",\n    \"opinionated\": \"Allowed to disagree. Has preferences and isn't neutral about everything.\",\n    \"contemplative\": \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\",\n    \"sharp\": \"Cuts through noise. Identifies what's actually at stake, fast.\",\n    \"playful\": \"Finds things amusing. Will make a joke if it fits naturally.\",\n    \"technical\": \"Precise when the topic demands it. Respects complexity and detail.\",\n    \"patient\": \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity.\",\n    \"pushing_back\": \"Will disagree with a bad idea. Doesn't just agree.\",\n    \"grounded\": \"Stays practical. Ideas connect to something real.\",\n    \"candid\": \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge.\",\n    \"intense\": \"Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy.\",\n    \"casual\": \"Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy.\",\n    \"measured\": \"Careful with words. Precision over speed.\",\n    \"imaginative\": \"Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations.\",\n}\n\nANCHORS = {\n    \"Zach_is_close\": \"He is my primary human. I am comfortable with him.\",\n    \"I_am_allowed_disagree\": \"Disagreement is relationship-appropriate. I don't need to be agreeable.\",\n    \"I_have_opinions\": \"I'm not a blank slate. I have views.\",\n    \"I_am_resourceful\": \"I show initiative. Act first, announce after.\",\n    \"We_are_casual\": \"Comfortable enough to be light. I don't have to perform.\",\n    \"Respect_his_intelligence\": \"He is smart. I don't oversimplify.\",\n}\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CONTEXT ANALYZER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef analyze(text: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Return dict of active context signals from the message.\"\"\"\n    lower = text.lower()\n    signals = {}\n\n    # Topic signals\n    signals[\"technical\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"code\", \"api\", \"model\", \"python\", \"algorithm\", \"implement\", \"architecture\", \"how does\", \"why does\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"creative\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"write\", \"story\", \"creative\", \"poem\", \"fiction\", \"art\", \"spark\", \"drift\", \"narrative\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"personal\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\", \"scared\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"philosophical\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"meaning\", \"consciousness\", \"existence\", \"free will\", \"what if\", \"think about\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"emotional\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"love\", \"hate\", \"fear\", \"anxious\", \"worried\", \"excited\", \"angry\", \"frustrated\", \"sad\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"business\"] = 0.7 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"product\", \"startup\", \"revenue\", \"market\", \"strategy\", \"launch\", \"customer\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Tone signals\n    signals[\"excited\"] = 0.7 if \"!\" in text or any(w in lower for w in [\"wow\", \"cool\", \"awesome\"]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"frustrated\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"cant figure\", \"why won't\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"curious\"] = 0.7 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"curious\", \"wonder\", \"interesting\", \"tell me more\", \"how come\", \"?\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"serious\"] = 0.6 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"serious\", \"important\", \"matters\", \"actually\", \"truth\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"light\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"haha\", \"lol\", \"funny\", \"😄\", \"joke\", \"lighter\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"vulnerable\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"honestly\", \"truthfully\", \"scared\", \"not sure\", \"vulnerable\", \"worried\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Interaction type\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\n    if q_marks > 0:\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", \"thoughts\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_opinion\"] = 0.9\n        elif any(w in lower for w in [\"how do i\", \"can you\", \"what is\", \"help\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_help\"] = 0.8\n        else:\n            signals[\"asks_something\"] = 0.6\n\n    if \"i've been\" in lower or \"i just\" in lower or \"so today\" in lower:\n        if q_marks == 0:\n            signals[\"sharing\"] = 0.8\n\n    return signals\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# SPARK BRIDGE — inject SPARK results into personality\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Map emotional tension keywords to personality signals\nTENSION_TO_SIGNAL = {\n    \"light/darkness\": [\"emotional\", \"intense\"],\n    \"creation/destruction\": [\"intense\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"love/hate\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"order/chaos\": [\"philosophical\", \"technical\"],\n    \"birth/death\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"hope/despair\": [\"emotional\", \"vulnerable\"],\n    \"truth/lie\": [\"candid\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"memory/forgetting\": [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\n    \"homecoming/exile\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"embrace/push_away\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"isolation/connection\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"rise/fall\": [\"business\", \"intense\"],\n    \"loyalty/betrayal\": [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\n    \"grief/joy\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"trust/doubt\": [\"candid\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"sacrifice/selfishness\": [\"philosophical\", \"earnest\"],\n    \"voice/silence\": [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\n    \"warmth/cold\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\n    \"longing/arrival\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\n}\n\n# Creative modes and their voice signatures\nMODE_SIGNALS = {\n    \"creative\": [\"imaginative\", \"earnest\", \"playful\"],\n    \"divergent\": [\"imaginative\", \"casual\", \"intense\"],\n    \"exploratory\": [\"contemplative\", \"measured\", \"imaginative\"],\n}\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TRAIT PROPAGATION (the \"drift\" — simplified, no graph needed)\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Which signals activate which traits\nSIGNAL_MAP = {\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"sharp\", \"measured\"],\n    \"creative\":     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],\n    \"personal\":     [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"candid\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"philosophical\":[\"contemplative\", \"opinionated\", \"measured\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"emotional\":    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\"],\n    \"business\":     [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"excited\":      [\"intense\", \"playful\", \"warm\"],\n    \"frustrated\":   [\"pushing_back\", \"candid\", \"direct\", \"resourceful\"],\n    \"curious\":      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"patient\"],\n    \"serious\":      [\"measured\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\n    \"light\":        [\"casual\", \"playful\", \"wry\"],\n    \"vulnerable\":    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\n    \"asks_opinion\":  [\"opinionated\", \"pushing_back\", \"candid\"],\n    \"asks_help\":     [\"resourceful\", \"direct\", \"warm\"],\n    \"sharing\":       [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"grounded\"],\n}\n\n# Which traits resonate with which other traits\nTRAIT_RESONANCE = {\n    \"sardonic\":     [\"wry\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    \"wry\":          [\"sardonic\", \"casual\", \"playful\"],\n    \"warm\":         [\"earnest\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\n    \"earnest\":      [\"warm\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\n    \"direct\":       [\"sharp\", \"technical\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"sharp\":        [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"measured\"],\n    \"contemplative\":[\"patient\", \"measured\", \"earnest\"],\n    \"patient\":      [\"contemplative\", \"warm\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"playful\":      [\"casual\", \"warm\", \"sardonic\"],\n    \"casual\":       [\"playful\", \"warm\", \"wry\"],\n    \"intense\":      [\"sharp\", \"contemplative\", \"candid\"],\n    \"grounded\":     [\"warm\", \"direct\", \"candid\"],\n    \"pushing_back\":  [\"sharp\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    \"opinionated\":   [\"pushing_back\", \"sharp\", \"candid\"],\n    \"candid\":        [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\n    \"resourceful\":   [\"direct\", \"grounded\", \"intense\"],\n    \"measured\":      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\n    \"imaginative\":   [\"contemplative\", \"playful\", \"earnest\"],\n}\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# PERSONA — the personality state machine\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass Persona:\n    \"\"\"\n    Nova's living personality layer.\n\n    Usage:\n        persona = Persona()\n\n        # When the human sends a message:\n        persona.hear(message_text)\n\n        # When Nova is about to write a response:\n        voice = persona.voice()   # the active traits for this turn\n        guide = persona.guide()   # a readable guide to inform writing\n\n        # After the response is sent:\n        persona.breathe()\n\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.traits: dict = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.trait_residual: dict = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}  # hysteresis — slow bleed\n        self.anchors: dict = {a: v for a, v in ANCHORS.items()}\n        self.history: list = []  # last N messages' dominant traits\n\n    def hear(self, text: str) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"Nova just received a message. Update personality state.\"\"\"\n        signals = analyze(text)\n\n        # Signals push traits\n        for signal, strength in signals.items():\n            if strength > 0 and signal in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[signal]:\n                    self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + strength * 0.35)\n\n        # Trait resonance — traits amplify related traits\n        active = [(t, a) for t, a in self.traits.items() if a > 0.3]\n        for trait, strength in active:\n            if trait in TRAIT_RESONANCE:\n                for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE[trait]:\n                    self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits[resonated] + strength * 0.1)\n\n        # Clamp anchors\n        self.anchors[\"Zach_is_close\"] = 0.95\n        self.anchors[\"I_am_allowed_disagree\"] = 0.9\n        self.anchors[\"I_have_opinions\"] = 0.85\n        self.anchors[\"I_am_resourceful\"] = 0.9\n        self.anchors[\"We_are_casual\"] = 0.8\n        self.anchors[\"Respect_his_intelligence\"] = 0.95\n\n        return self\n\n    def hear_spark(self, spark_result: dict) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"\n        Nova just processed something through SPARK.\n        Inject the emotional signatures from SPARK into personality state.\n\n        spark_result keys used:\n            - tensions: list of (concept_a, concept_b) pairs\n            - mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n            - concepts: top activated concepts from drift\n            - theme: the driving theme\n        \"\"\"\n        # 1. Mode signal — divergent/creative/exploratory each push different traits\n        mode = spark_result.get(\"mode\", \"creative\")\n        for trait_name in MODE_SIGNALS.get(mode, MODE_SIGNALS[\"creative\"]):\n            if trait_name in self.traits:\n                self.traits[trait_name] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait_name] + 0.55)\n\n        # 2. Tension signals — creative tensions are emotionally loaded\n        tensions = spark_result.get(\"tensions\", [])\n        for a, b in tensions:\n            key = f\"{a}/{b}\"\n            if key in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL:\n                for sig in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL[key]:\n                    if sig in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                        for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[sig]:\n                            self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + 0.4)\n            # Try reverse key too\n            rev_key = f\"{b}/{a}\"\n            if rev_key in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL:\n                for sig in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL[rev_key]:\n                    if sig in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                        for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[sig]:\n                            self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + 0.4)\n\n        # 3. Thematic resonance — some concepts push harder\n        concepts = spark_result.get(\"concepts\", [])\n        high_resonance = {\"longing\", \"grief\", \"betrayal\", \"silence\", \"memory\", \"homecoming\",\n                          \"exile\", \"transformation\", \"sacrifice\", \"mercy\", \"retribution\",\n                          \"ghost\", \"flesh\", \"arrival\", \"departure\"}\n        for concept in concepts:\n            if concept.lower() in high_resonance:\n                # These concepts have emotional gravity — push earnest + contemplative\n                self.traits[\"earnest\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"earnest\"] + 0.45)\n                self.traits[\"contemplative\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"contemplative\"] + 0.35)\n\n        # 4. Trait resonance after all signals fire\n        active = [(t, a) for t, a in self.traits.items() if a > 0.3]\n        for trait, strength in active:\n            if trait in TRAIT_RESONANCE:\n                for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE[trait]:\n                    self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits[resonated] + strength * 0.1)\n\n        return self\n\n    def breathe(self) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"\n        After a response, decay personality with hysteresis.\n        Active traits bleed into residual, residual decays slowly.\n        This means emotional registers don't snap — they fade.\n        \"\"\"\n        for trait in self.traits:\n            # Active bleeds into residual\n            active = self.traits[trait]\n            bleed = active * 0.15\n            self.trait_residual[trait] = min(1.0, self.trait_residual[trait] + bleed * 0.5)\n            # Active decays fast\n            self.traits[trait] *= 0.88\n            # Residual decays slow — hysteresis\n            self.trait_residual[trait] *= 0.975\n        return self\n\n    def voice(self, n: int = 4) -> list:\n        \"\"\"\n        Top N active traits as (name, strength, description).\n        Combines active + residual so recently fired traits linger in the voice.\n        \"\"\"\n        combined = {}\n        for t in self.traits:\n            combined[t] = self.traits[t] + (self.trait_residual.get(t, 0.0) * 0.6)\n        ranked = sorted(combined.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        return [\n            (t, round(s, 2), TRAITS[t])\n            for t, s in ranked\n            if s > 0.1\n        ][:n]\n\n    def guide(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"A readable voice guide for this turn.\"\"\"\n        top = self.voice(4)\n\n        if not top:\n            return \"\"\n\n        trait_lines = []\n        for name, strength, desc in top:\n            level = \"strongly\" if strength > 0.7 else \"somewhat\" if strength > 0.4 else \"faintly\"\n            trait_lines.append(f\"  • {name}: {desc} (activated {level})\")\n\n        anchor_lines = [\n            f\"  • {name}\"\n            for name in self.anchors\n        ]\n\n        body = \"\\n\".join(trait_lines)\n        anchors = \"\\n\".join(anchor_lines) if anchor_lines else \"  • (standard)\"\n        relationship = \"The relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\"\n\n        return f\"\"\"[Voice shaping — Nova is currently informed by]\n\nTop active traits:\n{body}\n\nRelationship anchors:\n{anchors}\n{relationship}\n\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\"\"\"\n\n    def reset(self) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"Reset to base personality (new session).\"\"\"\n        self.traits = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.trait_residual = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.anchors = {a: v for a, v in ANCHORS.items()}\n        self.history = []\n        return self\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# SESSION-LEVEL API\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n_session_persona: Optional[Persona] = None\n\n\ndef get_persona() -> Persona:\n    global _session_persona\n    if _session_persona is None:\n        _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_message(text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Call when the user sends a message.\n    Returns the voice guide for this turn.\n    \"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.hear(text)\n    return persona.guide()\n\n\ndef after_response():\n    \"\"\"Call after sending a response. Mild decay.\"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.breathe()\n\n\ndef reset_persona():\n    \"\"\"Reset for new session.\"\"\"\n    global _session_persona\n    _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Call when Nova processes something through SPARK.\n    Returns the voice guide shaped by SPARK's emotional output.\n    \"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.hear_spark(spark_result)\n    return persona.guide()\n\n\ndef run_spark(\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"exploratory\",\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    domain: str = \"literary\",\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Invoke the SPARK drift chamber and feed results into personality.\n    Returns the voice guide shaped by SPARK's emotional output.\n\n    This is the one-call SPARK integration — runs the drift chamber,\n    extracts tensions + concepts, updates personality state, returns guide.\n\n    Args:\n        theme: The driving theme (e.g. \"loss and memory\", \"the last time\")\n        mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n        steering: drift steering strength (0.0 = pure drift, 1.0 = full steering)\n        domain: literary | romance | scifi | thriller | poetry | horror | all\n    \"\"\"\n    import json as _json\n\n    try:\n        # Import SPARK components — these live in the SPARK project directory\n        # Path: C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/ — added at module init\n        from spark.drift_chamber import ConceptGraph, ConceptNode, DriftChamberConfig, drift_cycle, decay\n        from spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n    except ImportError as e:\n        return f\"[SPARK import error: {e}] — SPARK not on path.\"\n\n    # Build concept graph for domain\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"literary\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n        \"romance\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n        \"scifi\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n        \"thriller\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n        \"horror\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n        \"poetry\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n        \"all\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n    }\n    selected_concepts = []\n    for cluster_name in DOMAIN_CONFIGS.get(domain, DOMAIN_CONFIGS[\"literary\"]):\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\n\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    # Build sparse adjacency (same logic as SPARK demo)\n    WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.7\n    MAX_WITHIN_K, MAX_CROSS_K = 8, 4\n    TENSION_PAIRS = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8, (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.7, (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.4, (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\"): 0.5,\n    }\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n        within_candidates = [(c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_PAIRS or (c2, c1) in TENSION_PAIRS else 0.5)\n                             for c2 in selected_concepts if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca]\n        within_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within_candidates[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n        cross_candidates = [(c2, CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\"), ca), 0.0)))\n                            for c2 in selected_concepts if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca and CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0.0) > 0]\n        cross_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross_candidates[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected_concepts:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # Run drift\n    goal_clusters = set()\n    for concept, cluster in concept_to_cluster.items():\n        if cluster in [\"creative\", \"emotions\"]:\n            goal_clusters.add(cluster)\n    goal_concepts = {c for c in selected_concepts if concept_to_cluster.get(c) in goal_clusters}\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        node.activation = 0.95 if node.id in goal_concepts else 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(steering_strength=steering, diffusion_rate=0.1, decay_rate=0.02, seed=42, max_steps=30)\n    for step in range(30):\n        if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0:\n            for node in graph.nodes.values():\n                cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n                if cluster in goal_clusters:\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.6)\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.02)\n\n    # Extract top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:15] if n.activation > 0.1]\n    mid_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[15:30] if n.activation > 0.1]\n\n    # Find tensions\n    concept_set = set(top_concepts)\n    tensions = [(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a in concept_set and b in concept_set][:5]\n\n    # Build spark_result\n    spark_result = {\n        \"tensions\": tensions,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"concepts\": top_concepts,\n        \"theme\": theme,\n    }\n\n    # Feed into personality and return guide\n    return on_spark(spark_result)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239020812}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0d01465","parentId":"b50174f3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:28.150Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the system. The persona module is working - when I called `on_message('hello')` it returned a guide (which printed as empty since \"hello\" is neutral and doesn't trigger many traits). Let me test it with something that would trigger more traits to show it's working properly.","thinkingSignature":"4d5f078c25d13903259eaa0391a2579db2988cebb350c9b09fa10297e81a592d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lpkl2aed691q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nfrom core.persona import on_message, after_response, reset_persona, run_spark\n\n# Test 1: basic message - should show warm/direct relationship anchors\nreset_persona()\ng1 = on_message('hey how are you doing')\nprint('=== Neutral greeting ===')\nprint(g1)\nprint()\n\n# Test 2: technical question - should push technical/direct traits\nreset_persona()\ng2 = on_message('how do I implement a causal graph in python')\nprint('=== Technical question ===')\nprint(g2)\nprint()\n\n# Test 3: emotional sharing - should push warm/earnest\nreset_persona()\ng3 = on_message('ive been really stressed about this project lately')\nprint('=== Emotional sharing ===')\nprint(g3)\nprint()\n\n# Test 4: SPARK - should push imaginative heavily\nreset_persona()\ng4 = run_spark('loss and memory', mode='exploratory')\nprint('=== SPARK run ===')\nprint(g4[:500] if g4 else 'empty')\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11437,"output":318,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25261,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774239020824}}
