ect: No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters. (activated faintly)\r\n  � sharp: Cuts through noise. Identifies what's actually at stake, fast. (activated faintly)\r\n  � measured: Careful with words. Precision over speed. (activated faintly)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\r\n\r\n=== Emotional sharing ===\r\n\r\n\r\n=== SPARK run ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated strongly)\r\n  � measured: Careful with words. Precision over speed. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � imaginative: Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations. (activated somewhat)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  �","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239029074}}
{"type":"message","id":"510933f0","parentId":"e8f63614","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:10:51.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The persona system is working:\n1. Neutral greeting → empty (no strong signals)\n2. Technical question → technical/direct/sharp/measured traits activate\n3. Emotional sharing → empty? Let me check why...\n4. SPARK → contemplative/measured/earnest/imaginative - that's working\n\nThe emotional sharing came back empty. Let me check why - \"ive been really stressed about this project lately\" should trigger \"personal\" signal (which activates warm/earnest/candid/grounded). Let me debug this.\n\nActually, looking at the analyze function:\n```python\nsignals[\"personal\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n    \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\", \"scared\"\n\n\n]) else 0.0\n```\n\n\"ive been really stressed\" - \"i've been\" matches! But let me check the `on_message` return - it returns `persona.guide()` which requires `voice(n=4)` to have items. And `voice` requires combined score > 0.1. So the issue is the trait resonance - personal signal goes to warm/earnest/candid/grounded, and those need to accumulate enough strength to show up in the voice output.\n\nThe SPARK run is showing contemplative, measured, earnest, imaginative - those are strong signals. The neutral greeting has no strong signals. But the emotional sharing should have triggered personal signals, so either the SIGNAL_MAP doesn't have enough trait propagation or the hysteresis isn't strong enough to maintain them. Let me trace through the code flow more carefully. When I call `on_message`, it creates a new Persona via `get_persona()`, calls `hear()` on it, then returns the guide. But if `reset_persona()` was called first, that creates a fresh session persona without any history, so the emotional state from that previous context might not be carrying over properly.\n\nLooking at the test output for \"ive been really stressed about this project lately\" - the `hear()` method processes the text and finds matches like \"i've been\" and \"really stressed\", but the guide is still returning empty. The issue seems to be in how the signals are being detected or how they're supposed to propagate to the voice output.\n\nThe problem might be that the emoji in the guide formatting isn't being handled correctly by the console, so even though signals are being found (like the personal signal from \"i've been\"), the resulting traits aren't reaching the threshold needed to generate non-empty voice output. Let me trace through the actual signal detection to see what's being matched. to the guide output correctly in my test. Let me just confirm the system is working based on what I already saw: technical questions activate technical/direct/sharp/measured, SPARK triggers contemplative/measured/earnest/imaginative, and neutral/short messages produce empty guides as expected.\n\nThe emotional sharing returning empty is puzzling—\"ive been really stressed\" should trigger the personal signal from \"i've been\" and the frustrated signal from \"stressed\", but something's preventing that from working. Rather than debug further right now, I should report to Zach that the core system is functioning: technical and creative prompts work well, and I'll mention the neutral greeting behavior is actually correct.\n\nLooking at the voice guide output, it seems the guide is being generated but something in the print pipeline is breaking the formatting, stripping out the trait characters and boxes. The character encoding looks fine when I print it directly, so the issue might be in how the guide is being constructed or passed through. Let me trace through what's actually being returned to see where the formatting gets lost. → signal detected → traits updated → guide generated → after_response called → hysteresis decay\n\nThe hook in hooks/persona-voice/ fires on message:preprocessed, but I need to figure out if it's actually being invoked during normal conversation. Looking at the test results, the core mechanics work: technical prompts activate technical/direct traits, SPARK engages the contemplative/earnest/imaginative pathway, and neutral greetings correctly produce no output. The system seems sound, so I should report these findings to Zach.","thinkingSignature":"ff65ee13db07601d4b26dc22929b80d8f80885c98fe97c8fdd5f691f2dd26ca8"},{"type":"text","text":"The core pipeline is working — here's what I confirmed:\n\n**Technical question** → `technical`, `direct`, `sharp`, `measured` activate (correct)\n\n**SPARK run** → `contemplative`, `measured`, `earnest`, `imaginative` activate (correct — the tension detection and mode signals are feeding through properly)\n\n**Neutral greeting** → correctly returns empty (no signals triggered)\n\n**One issue I'm seeing:** emotional/personal messages like \"I've been really stressed\" are coming back empty when they should push `warm`/`earnest`. The signal detection fires but the traits don't accumulate above threshold. Let me check the bleed-down:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xf3huqqq1uxr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nfrom core.persona import Persona\n\np = Persona()\np.hear('ive been really stressed about this project lately')\nprint('signals:', p.hear('ive been really stressed about this project lately').__class__)\np.hear('ive been really stressed about this project lately')\nprint('traits after hear:', {t: round(v,3) for t,v in p.traits.items() if v > 0})\nprint('voice:', p.voice())\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12067,"output":1123,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26696,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774239029082}}
