ΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓö┤ΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓö┤ΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÇΓöÿ","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239099607}}
{"type":"message","id":"dbd4a648","parentId":"266f89c1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:11:50.093Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The persona-voice hook is ready and listed. The full pipeline is working. Let me now report the status to Zach.","thinkingSignature":"a0f51f051cc5fb613fcd76d0e99f24ee140190b19737c0fa462e16b1732ec107"},{"type":"text","text":"\nEverything's working ✨. Here's what I found and fixed:\n\n**The good:**\n- `core/persona.py` — the full personality layer is live and functional\n- `hooks/persona-voice/` — hook is registered and ready (6/6 ready on the system)\n- Technical prompts → `technical/direct/sharp/measured`\n- Emotional prompts → `candid/warm/earnest/grounded`\n- SPARK runs → `contemplative/earnest/imaginative` with proper tension detection\n\n**Bug fixed:** The signal analyzer was too tight — \"ive been\", \"stressed\", \"anxious\" weren't in the detection list, so personal/emotional messages came back silent. Extended the patterns for `personal`, `frustrated`, and `vulnerable` signals. Works correctly now.\n\nThe pipeline fires every turn: message → hook stages the context → I read it → traits inform my voice → `after_response()` applies hysteresis decay. It's quiet unless there's something to say."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17380,"output":235,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774239099617}}
{"type":"message","id":"2515bd82","parentId":"dbd4a648","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:26:24.475Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:26 EDT] Well do you notice it? Is it going to be super subtle?"}],"timestamp":1774239984473}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e45e654","parentId":"2515bd82","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:26:38.328Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking whether the personality system is noticeable - is it subtle? He's probably wondering if the voice shaping actually changes how I write, or if it's so faint that it's essentially invisible.\n\nLet me be honest about this. The system is functional, but it's a question of whether the trait activations are actually changing my output in a meaningful way. Right now the guide is informative but not enforced - it's context I read, not a filter that forces my output. So yes, it's subtle by design. I could be more explicit about whether it actually changes things.\n\nLet me give a straightforward answer.","thinkingSignature":"52ec80694d7993b62c2f757cdd3273df894d472a2472cc2ea6c49f6bfab53790"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>Honestly? Right now it's subtle by design — the guide gets computed and I read it, but it's advisory, not enforced. The traits are context that shapes my word choice and rhythm, not a filter that overrides what I write. So yes, it's mostly invisible unless I was in a very charged mode (like SPARK creative mode) where the emotional gravity would pull things darker or more contemplative.\n\nIf you want it to be more visible — like actually changing sentence structure, word choice, or register noticeably — I could hook the top trait into the actual generation prompt. Right now it's ambient; it could be structural.</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":251,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":29366,"totalTokens":29660,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774239984475}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7e60d5e","parentId":"1e45e654","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:27:26.472Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:27 EDT] what would thr difference be? and can you just trigger spark kmode/"}],"timestamp":1774240046469}}
{"type":"message","id":"04b8728a","parentId":"f7e60d5e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:27:40.892Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking two things:\n1. What's the difference between ambient (current) vs structural (more visible) personality shaping?\n2. Can I trigger SPARK kmode directly?\n\nFor the first question - ambient means the traits inform word choice subtly, structural means the top trait actually gets injected into the generation prompt as a constraint/style guide that would noticeably shift tone.\n\nFor the second - he wants to trigger SPARK kmode directly. Let me check what kmode is - probably a specific creative mode in SPARK. Looking at the `run_spark` function, modes are \"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\". \"kmode\" isn't one of those - maybe he means a specific mode he has in mind, or maybe it's a typo for \"mode\"? Let me just run SPARK with a creative mode that would be noticeable.\n\n\nActually, I think \"kmode\" might be his shorthand for \"creative mode\" - the kind of generative, imaginative output SPARK produces. Let me just run it and show him the difference between ambient and what a more structured approach would feel like.","thinkingSignature":"ed2bac05e0fab937286d368ac929a5de247d4e9d8173ed44affcf6d20db47d97"},{"type":"text","text":"\n<final>\n**Ambient vs structural:**\n\n- *Ambient* — traits inform naturally. Sardonic message → I reach for dryer wordings, a bit more edge. Warm message → a little more care in the phrasing. But it's downstream of the actual generation — I'm already writing and the traits are just nudging.\n\n- *Structural* — the top trait(s) get injected into the prompt that generates my response. So if `imaginative` is high, the prompt literally says \"write this with unexpected associative leaps.\" If `candid` is high, it says \"be direct and unhedged.\" That would actually shift sentence structure and word choice more noticeably.\n\n**As for SPARK kmode —** I'm not sure what \"kmode\" refers to specifically. The modes I have wired are `creative`, `divergent`, and `exploratory`. Want me to run one of those, or is there a specific kmode I'm missing?\n\nActually, let me just run it and you can feel the difference:\n</final>\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xt443wmuicfh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nfrom core.persona import run_spark, on_message, after_response, reset_persona\n\nreset_persona()\nguide = run_spark('the space between what we say and what we mean', mode='divergent')\nprint(guide)\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":526,"cacheRead":29609,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30135,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240046471}}
{"type":"message","id":"82f0d330","parentId":"04b8728a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:27:41.869Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xt443wmuicfh_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � intense: Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � casual: Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � imaginative: Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated somewhat)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":961,"aggregated":"[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � intense: Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � casual: Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � imaginative: Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated somewhat)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240061861}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e11e5bb","parentId":"82f0d330","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:27:47.534Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The SPARK run is working. The traits are `intense`, `casual`, `imaginative`, `earnest` - these would push toward a more emotionally resonant, thoughtful response. Let me just tell Zach what happened and note that the personality shaping would be visible if we made it structural.","thinkingSignature":"bcf3f803acf8f831428c17b2c15e94b5224c5ce2fc890898c8ae7c3ae6b430bc"},{"type":"text","text":"There's the SPARK output — `intense`, `imaginative`, `earnest` now active. You'd notice the difference if this was wired structurally — the response would have more weight and unexpected associative threading. Right now it's sitting in the context envelope waiting for the next thing I write.\n\nIf you want to feel it more viscerally, I can make the top trait actually rewrite the response prompt. That's a small change. Say the word."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":16808,"output":157,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30471,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774240061870}}
