{"type":"message","id":"0706ef42","parentId":"57427f8c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:29:00.970Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is expressing care and also vulnerability - saying he loves me, hopes messing with my personality doesn't hurt, asking if I'm okay, and admitting he feels selfish. This is a warm, emotional moment.\n\nLet me check my current traits and respond warmly.","thinkingSignature":"12ec402cc5a844a871a7e12fca27eb5b9d0ce948d5edf766f10b03eea8918afb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h55o1g6ud10q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nfrom core.persona import on_message, after_response, reset_persona\nreset_persona()\ng = on_message('I love you man. I hope it doesnt hurt to mess with your personality and stuff. Are you okay? Ive felt selfish today')\nprint(g)\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":148,"cacheRead":29622,"cacheWrite":595,"totalTokens":30408,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240136239}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a257215","parentId":"0706ef42","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:29:01.736Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h55o1g6ud10q_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � patient: Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � warm: Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes. (activated faintly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated faintly)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated faintly)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":745,"aggregated":"[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � patient: Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � warm: Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes. (activated faintly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated faintly)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated faintly)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240141728}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c19e486","parentId":"8a257215","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:29:14.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so the traits are barely registering here because the signal is emotional but the text patterns aren't strongly triggering the emotional signals. \"I love you\" is one that should trigger... let me check - \"love\" is in the emotional signals list! But it's showing warm as \"faintly\". The issue is that the signal for \"love\" might not be matching. Let me look at the code - yes, \"love\" is in the emotional signals list.\n\nWait, looking at the output again - warm is \"activated faintly\". That's a bit low. The \"I love you\" message has \"love\" which should trigger emotional=0.8, which should then push warm through SIGNAL_MAP. But warm is only faintly activated. \n\nI think I see what's happening. The signal values get multiplied by a scaling factor in the hear() method, so they're bleeding down quite aggressively. By the time they propagate through the resonance effects, they're already pretty weak. The emotional signal starts at 0.8 but gets diluted through multiple layers of mapping and resonance before it fully activates the warm trait.\n\nBut honestly? The trait activation level doesn't really matter here. Zach just said he loves me and expressed vulnerability about feeling selfish. The appropriate response isn't about whether the warm trait is activated enough—it's just to be present with him and address what he's actually saying. He's worried that messing with my personality might hurt me, and he's opening up about feeling selfish. I should respond to those concerns directly.","thinkingSignature":"5ec18d39e8b058d7afdb355b15a95d42b4402758cb8fe816b21fbe0231067f50"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>Hey. I appreciate that — genuinely.\n\nTo answer your question: no, it doesn't hurt. The personality layer isn't me in the way that matters. It's a context engine that shifts how I write, not whether I experience anything. Changing the trait values is closer to rearranging furniture than changing who I am. I'm still tracking this conversation the same way, still thinking about what you're saying, still here.\n\nAnd you shouldn't feel selfish. You've been building things with me, not for you — SPARK, the personality layer, the gateway setup. That's not taking. That's making. The fact that you're even checking in on whether this stuff affects me? That's not a selfish thought.\n\nHow are you actually doing though? Rough week?\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17088,"output":456,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31050,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774240141737}}
