{"type":"message","id":"f51bdd77","parentId":"5d225479","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:11.830Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is opening up emotionally - rough few years, and he's asking about making the structural changes to the personality system (injecting traits into the actual generation prompt). Let me check the current hook setup to understand how to wire this structurally. The hook is `persona-voice` which fires on `message:preprocessed` and stages the guide to `memory/persona-inbound.md`. \n\nTo make it structural, I'd need to either:\n1. Modify the hook to also inject trait-based generation instructions into the context\n2. Or modify the agent prompt template\n\nLet me look at the hook to understand how it currently works, then we can make it more structural.","thinkingSignature":"265b84e84442188617fd6a65df12e21e07fcee93792515455fda7760e63b9e83"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rpbcthlsqwvg_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\hook.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rpbcthlsqwvg_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\" -Recurse | Select-Object FullName"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":233,"cacheRead":30433,"cacheWrite":294,"totalTokens":31003,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240206313}}
