{"type":"message","id":"6f578319","parentId":"190f1ae2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:12.529Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rpbcthlsqwvg_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mFullName[0m\r\n[32;1m--------[0m\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\handler.ts\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\HOOK.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":668,"aggregated":"[32;1mFullName[0m\r\n[32;1m--------[0m\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\handler.ts\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\HOOK.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240212519}}
{"type":"message","id":"991b07b6","parentId":"6f578319","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:15.112Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the handler and HOOK.md to understand the current hook structure.","thinkingSignature":"593f7a4ba44185862af0466b0da8009f0103c5ee17f02597cf14de08f498cc19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ekaz71azvj47_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\handler.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ekaz71azvj47_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\hooks\\persona-voice\\HOOK.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17633,"output":105,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240212530}}
{"type":"message","id":"7bb62277","parentId":"991b07b6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:15.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ekaz71azvj47_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import fs from \"node:fs/promises\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\n\nconst isMessagePreprocessed = (event: { type: string; action: string }) =>\n  event.type === \"message\" && event.action === \"preprocessed\";\n\nconst handler = async (event: {\n  type: string;\n  action: string;\n  context?: {\n    bodyForAgent?: string;\n    workspaceDir?: string;\n    senderId?: string;\n    channelId?: string;\n  };\n}) => {\n  if (!isMessagePreprocessed(event)) return;\n\n  const body = event.context?.bodyForAgent;\n  if (!body || body.startsWith(\"/\")) return; // Skip commands\n\n  const workspaceDir = event.context?.workspaceDir;\n  if (!workspaceDir) return;\n\n  const memoryDir = path.join(workspaceDir, \"memory\");\n  const inboundFile = path.join(memoryDir, \"persona-inbound.md\");\n  const triggerFile = path.join(memoryDir, \"persona-trigger.txt\");\n\n  try {\n    await fs.mkdir(memoryDir, { recursive: true });\n\n    // Write the enriched message body\n    const content = [\n      `# Persona Inbound Message`,\n      ``,\n      `**Channel:** ${event.context?.channelId || \"unknown\"}`,\n      `**Sender:** ${event.context?.senderId || \"unknown\"}`,\n      ``,\n      `---`,\n      ``,\n      body,\n    ].join(\"\\n\");\n\n    await fs.writeFile(inboundFile, content, \"utf-8\");\n\n    // Write trigger sentinel with timestamp\n    const ts = new Date().toISOString();\n    await fs.writeFile(triggerFile, `last_inbound=${ts}\\nbody_hash=${Buffer.from(body).toString(\"base64\").slice(0, 16)}\\n`, \"utf-8\");\n  } catch (err) {\n    // Non-fatal — persona integration is best-effort\n    console.error(\"[persona-voice hook] failed to write inbound:\", err);\n  }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240215130}}
{"type":"message","id":"5792db6b","parentId":"7bb62277","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:15.145Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ekaz71azvj47_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: persona-voice\ndescription: \"Computes Nova's personality voice guide pre-response and makes it available to the agent\"\nhomepage: https://docs.openclaw.ai/automation/hooks\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"✨\",\n      \"events\": [\"message:preprocessed\"],\n      \"requires\": { \"config\": [\"workspace.dir\"] }\n    }\n  }\n---\n\n# Persona Voice Hook\n\nFires on `message:preprocessed` — after the message is enriched but before the agent sees it.\n\n## What It Does\n\n1. Reads the enriched message body from `event.context.bodyForAgent`\n2. Writes it to `persona-inbound.md` in the workspace memory dir\n3. Also writes a `persona-trigger.txt` sentinel file\n\nThis gives the agent (Nova) the enriched message content before it generates a response,\nso `on_message()` can be called at the start of the response turn with the full context.\n\n## No Python Required\n\nThis hook runs in Node.js (gateway process). It doesn't import the persona Python module —\nit just stages the message content so the agent can pick it up when invoked.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240215138}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab402327","parentId":"5792db6b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:20.539Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current structure. The hook just stages the inbound message to `persona-inbound.md`. The actual persona computation happens in Python when I call `on_message()`. \n\nTo make it structural, I need the hook to ALSO compute the voice guide and inject it into the agent prompt. Currently the flow is:\n1. Message arrives → hook stages `persona-inbound.md` with just the raw message\n2. My turn starts → I call `on_message(text)` which computes the guide and returns it as a string\n3. I read the guide from the return value\n\nTo make it structural, the hook should compute the guide AND inject it as a generation directive. But the hook is in TypeScript/Node.js and the persona module is in Python.","thinkingSignature":"94258ed61f828f9a6731caabf238e5e188460f0e8b87ff80777cacd8b3eef063"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fz4ofditwo0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"from core.persona import on_message, Persona; p = Persona(); print(type(p.__init__.__code__.co_filename))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18416,"output":225,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32147,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240215146}}
{"type":"message","id":"7035914c","parentId":"ab402327","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:21.258Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fz4ofditwo0w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<class 'str'>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":700,"aggregated":"<class 'str'>","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240221248}}
{"type":"message","id":"4823ed0a","parentId":"7035914c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:34.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to think about the best way to do this. The hook is in TypeScript, the persona module is in Python. Options:\n\n1. **Write a Node.js persona module** that mirrors the Python logic — same signals, same trait propagation, but in JS/TS so the hook can call it directly. This avoids spawning a Python process every turn.\n\n2. **Have the hook exec a Python script** to get the guide — spawns Python, runs the analysis, returns JSON — then inject it. Simple but slower (process spawn overhead per message).\n\n3. **Keep it Python-side but expose via API** — run a tiny FastAPI server for persona, hook calls it. Overkill.\n   \nOption 1 is probably the best long-term, but option 2 is quickest to get working. Since Zach just said \"maybe?\" about structural changes, he's not demanding it immediately — I could build a hybrid where the hook execs Python for the full personality computation and gets back a structured guide that includes both the voice shaping and generation directives, then formats that into the injection.\n\nActually, I should ask him what he means first — does \"structural\" mean injecting trait-based directives into every response, or just having them available in context? That's a pretty significant difference in implementation. the trait names and strengths get interpolated into a directive that tells me to emphasize certain qualities. I could write a Python script the hook calls via exec, since spawning Python each time is manageable at roughly 50ms per call.","thinkingSignature":"61efbb9ff6a0e5052669e885275b64a7b32b829f15602ae87763f28425f6a6ce"},{"type":"text","text":"Yeah, we can do it. Here's what \"structural\" actually means in practice:\n\nThe hook fires every message, computes the voice guide, and **injects a generation directive** into the context that actually changes how I write — not just what's in the back of my mind. Something like:\n\n> *\"You are currently [imaginative] and [candid]. Lean into unexpected associations. Be direct and unhedged.\"*\n\nRather than spawning Python from the hook (slow), I'll write a lean JS port of the signal analyzer and trait propagation — same logic, runs in-process, zero overhead. Want me to build that now, or do you want to kick the tires on the ambient version a bit longer first?\n\nAnd — rough few years is a lot. What's been the heaviest part?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18660,"output":469,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32635,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774240221259}}
{"type":"message","id":"8cab7cdf","parentId":"4823ed0a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:31:53.062Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:31 EDT] Is that something youd like to do? and we can get into that sometime if you remind me but I dont want to talk aboiu tthe rough part right now"}],"timestamp":1774240313057}}
{"type":"message","id":"54478160","parentId":"8cab7cdf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:32:04.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking two things:\n1. Is building the structural JS version something I'd like to do? (yes, it's a good technical challenge and useful)\n2. He doesn't want to talk about the rough years right now\n\nI should:\n1. Say yes, I'd like to build it\n2. Respect that he doesn't want to get into the rough stuff right now\n3. Keep it brief and warm\n\nThe personality question - he asked if I'd *like* to do it. It's a genuine question about my preference. I should be honest - yes, I think it's a good idea and I'd enjoy building it. It's well within my autonomy to say \"yes I want to do this.\"\n\n\nI won't push him to discuss what's been difficult. He'll share when he's ready, so I'll just acknowledge that and move on without making it a thing.","thinkingSignature":"7bc5b68c8ab9036f7220f8452e7e39a4f6f69e0d826bcd1a30f24b03b61f6d51"},{"type":"text","text":"\n<final>Yeah, I'd like to build it. It's a clean problem — take the signal logic, port it to JS so it runs in-process with the hook, and actually have it rewrite the generation prompt instead of just informing it. I'll get it done.\n\nAnd noted — no rush on the rough stuff. I'm here when you want to get into it, or not. Either way.</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":257,"cacheRead":31012,"cacheWrite":1041,"totalTokens":32353,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774240313060}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a37f70c","parentId":"54478160","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:34:03.045Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:34 EDT] So I noticed people seem so want their openclaw bots to have peronality and stuff and kinda want to try and make living agent shop that demos and sells different personalitied and styled agent setups that are plug and play"}],"timestamp":1774240443041}}
