l\nneokarma-soulmd-builder  Neokarma Soul.md Builder\nSummary: Persistent personality for AI agents — define, evolve, and share your soul\nOwner: veiovi\nCreated: 2026-02-18T07:05:37.460Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T21:30:40.010Z\nLatest: 1.4.5\nTags: latest=1.4.5","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240840394}}
{"type":"message","id":"b675f743","parentId":"8beb5c38","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:40:40.410Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rtlcxuhul3et_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\naura  AURA\nSummary: Configure AI personality using the AURA protocol (HEXACO-based). Use when user wants to customize agent personality, reduce sycophancy, adjust communication style, or mentions AURA/personality configuration.\nOwner: phiro56\nCreated: 2026-02-01T00:40:36.636Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T22:45:35.927Z\nLatest: 0.1.0-beta.1\nTags: beta=0.1.0-beta.1, latest=0.1.0-beta.1\n===\r\n- Fetching skill\npersonality  Personality\nSummary: Discover your DISC personality type and install personalized AI communication skills. Use when someone mentions personality, communication style, DISC, how AI should talk to them, how to communicate with a coworker/boss/teammate, preparing for a meeting or difficult conversation, or wants to customize their AI experience. Also triggers on: 'what's my personality type', 'set up my personality', 'personality quiz', 'how should I talk to', 'communication coaching'. Includes interactive quizzes for both flows. Powered by Crystal's DISC framework.\nOwner: lukethomas14\nCreated: 2026-02-02T20:15:29.950Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-26T03:27:21.120Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nTags: latest=1.0.0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4160,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\naura  AURA\nSummary: Configure AI personality using the AURA protocol (HEXACO-based). Use when user wants to customize agent personality, reduce sycophancy, adjust communication style, or mentions AURA/personality configuration.\nOwner: phiro56\nCreated: 2026-02-01T00:40:36.636Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T22:45:35.927Z\nLatest: 0.1.0-beta.1\nTags: beta=0.1.0-beta.1, latest=0.1.0-beta.1\n===\r\n- Fetching skill\npersonality  Personality\nSummary: Discover your DISC personality type and install personalized AI communication skills. Use when someone mentions personality, communication style, DISC, how AI should talk to them, how to communicate with a coworker/boss/teammate, preparing for a meeting or difficult conversation, or wants to customize their AI experience. Also triggers on: 'what's my personality type', 'set up my personality', 'personality quiz', 'how should I talk to', 'communication coaching'. Includes interactive quizzes for both flows. Powered by Crystal's DISC framework.\nOwner: lukethomas14\nCreated: 2026-02-02T20:15:29.950Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-26T03:27:21.120Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nTags: latest=1.0.0","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240840401}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab102afa","parentId":"b675f743","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:40:51.447Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at some of the key projects to understand what Zach has. Let me check MEMORY.md for the projects, and look at the projects list. I also need to understand what ClawHub has that's most similar.\n\nThe competitive landscape:\n1. `personality-switcher` — static persona presets\n2. `open-persona` — meta-skill framework for persona packs\n3. `agent-soul-crafter` — SOUL.md template builder\n4. `neokarma-soulmd-builder` — persistent personality, evolve/share\n5. `aura` — HEXACO-based personality config\n6. `personality` — DISC-based personality quiz + skills\n\n\n7. `personality-analysis-yang` — personality analysis\n\nWhat Zach has that they don't:\n- **Context-reactive trait propagation** (signals → traits → voice)\n- **SPARK emotional engine** — tensions, modes, thematic drift\n- **Hysteresis** — personality state persists across turns with slow decay\n- **hook-based integration** — runs every message pre-response\n\nThis is fundamentally different from template-based approaches. Now I'm thinking through what could actually be built and monetized here, so let me run SPARK to brainstorm this properly.","thinkingSignature":"12a5f079a332a30727bf21f3100febd2384543c3d05fc4957f85bc4bcb4295a9"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me hit SPARK for the real brainstorm:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m45iq6hguysf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nfrom core.persona import run_spark, on_message, after_response, reset_persona\n\n# Heavy brainstorm session — divergent mode for max creative range\nreset_persona()\nguide = run_spark(\n    'a marketplace where AI personalities are living, breathing, context-aware entities — not static templates',\n    mode='divergent',\n    steering=0.4,\n    domain='all'\n)\nprint(guide)\n\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26542,"output":393,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40441,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240840411}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3b63a48","parentId":"ab102afa","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:40:52.632Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m45iq6hguysf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � intense: Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � casual: Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � imaginative: Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated somewhat)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1159,"aggregated":"[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � intense: Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � casual: Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � imaginative: Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated somewhat)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240852619}}
{"type":"message","id":"36ade68e","parentId":"c3b63a48","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:40:57.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now look at the projects themselves to understand the landscape better. Let me check MEMORY.md for project details and the project list.","thinkingSignature":"c1dfccaf4d2a863196e4a88cb8112b8385dbb6ba6bdd652023d2011673c85f1c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qbl6zfbvbit5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\projects.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27114,"output":70,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40690,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240852633}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f5af6b3","parentId":"36ade68e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:40:57.418Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qbl6zfbvbit5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Projects — Full Inventory\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n---\n\n## 📂 Project Locations\n\n```\nC:/dev/\n├── EXP/                     → KVict (rebranded)\n├── component-crate/\n├── shared-browser/\n├── COG-research/\n├── mind-agent/\n├── infant/\n├── mind/\n├── temporal-attention/\n├── selfhelper-main/\n├── tta-crypto/\n└── werender/\n\nC:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/\n├── architecture-4-wide-shallow/\n├── architecture-5-hypergraph/\n├── architecture-6-global-workspace-hive/\n└── (causal-minimal/ to be created)\n\nOther:\n├── C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/memory/     ← Claw's daily session logs\n└── ~/Claw/ (root Claw workspace)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 💰 MONETIZATION / PRODUCT\n\n### KVict (formerly EXP/CAAE)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/EXP/` (rebranded to KVict)\n**What:** AI inference optimization platform — KV cache + GPU cost/SLA optimizer for vLLM\n**B2B claims (proven):** 3.0x throughput, 64% memory reduction, 54% P99 latency improvement, 98%+ SLA, 43% cost reduction\n**Consumer claims:** 3.6x more requests, 0% contradictions, 5x token efficiency\n**Stack:** Python vLLM plugin (600+ lines) + FastAPI advisor service + React dashboard\n**Docs:** ✅ Excellent — landing page, proven claims, architecture, deployment guides, benchmark repro\n**Status:** Production-ready, well-documented, B2B + consumer positioning\n**Key files:** `docs/experiments/BREAKTHROUGH_EXPERIMENTS.md`, `docs/reference/PROVEN_CLAIMS.md`\n**Evidence:** experiment_7, 9, 11, 13 JSON results committed\n\n### Component Crate\n**Location:** `C:/dev/component-crate/`\n**What:** VS Code extension — save, search, reuse Tailwind + React components. GitHub import. Freemium.\n**Plans:** Free (10), Hobby ($5/mo, 50), Pro ($15/mo, 200), Team ($49/mo, unlimited). GitHub imports free.\n**Status:** SPEC written, extension built, marketplace not yet published\n**Docs:** README good. Roadmap items pending (web dashboard, marketplace, team sync)\n**URL:** componentcrate.com (live landing page)\n**⚠️ Issue:** README says \"coming soon\" for marketplace — needs publishing\n\n### Shared Browser\n**Location:** `C:/dev/shared-browser/`\n**What:** Playwright browser embedded in webpage, both see + control same browser in real-time\n**Stack:** Python server + Playwright + web frontend\n**Status:** Working server, basic controls (navigate, scroll, back/forward, screenshot)\n**Docs:** ⚠️ README only — no internal docs\n**Missing:** Screenshot sharing, click coordination, form filling, WebSocket real-time sync\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 RESEARCH / ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Mind (Cognitive AI)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/mind/`\n**What:** Self-sufficient cognitive AI — no external LLMs or APIs. Thinks, learns, adapts autonomously.\n**Modules:** Cognitive reflexes, neural substrate (curiosity/caution/urgency), conscious reasoning, episodic/declarative/procedural memory, autonomous research, self-healing\n**Stack:** Python 3.11+, pip installable\n**Status:** Active development\n**Docs:** ✅ README good, clear architecture diagram\n\n### Infant (Synthetic Cognition)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/infant/`\n**What:** Synthetic human cognitive architecture with persistent identity. Dual-head (core frozen / flexible learning). 4-tier memory. Dreams for consolidation.\n**Experiments:** 10/10 pass — mirror test, continuity, body ownership, value formation/stability, memory persistence, personality coherence, integration, fracture prevention\n**License:** MIT\n**Status:** Published\n**Docs:** ✅ README excellent — architecture diagram, experiment table, quick start code\n\n### COG-Research (Imagination + Self-Model)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/COG-research/`\n**What:** Two frameworks:\n1. **Imagination-First Learning** — counterfactual worlds via transition operators T_θ with internal coherence\n2. **Minimal Self-Model First** — world modeling emerges as perturbation to self-prediction\n**Data:** Timeseries-PILE (13M+ time series), ETT, Traffic, Weather\n**Status:** Validated training pipelines on ETT datasets\n**Docs:** README + TIMESERIES_PILE_INTEGRATION.md\n**⚠️ Note:** Large data/ checkpoints — likely in data/, results/, checkpoints/ subdirs\n\n### TemporalAttention Store\n**Location:** `C:/dev/temporal-attention/` (as `event_store/`)\n**What:** Memory system combining time + events + focus for smarter retrieval. Unique focus decay.\n**Results:** 10/10 hard scenario tests passed (SimpleRAG gets 6/10)\n**What makes it unique:** Focus decay — no other system has it\n**Docs:** ✅ README good — problem table, formula, benchmark results, quick start\n\n### Selfhelper-Main (Self-Improving Agent)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/selfhelper-main/`\n**What:** Autonomous agent with tool invention, self-distillation, web + arXiv research, remote worker execution\n**Key features:**\n- LLM provider abstraction + Minimax OpenAI adapter\n- Tool registry (versioned, autonomous invention)\n- Hybrid distillation: online per-iteration + nightly packaging\n- Evaluators: strict schema checks + backward-compatible command mode\n- GitHub Actions CI: auto-improve nightly + smoke tests\n**Stack:** Python, pyproject.toml, self_improving_agent package\n**Artfolders:** Many artifacts_* folders — different experiment runs (final_auto, new_auto, cmd, mock, web3, etc.)\n**Docs:** ✅ README thorough + IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md\n\n### Mind-Agent Service\n**Location:** `C:/dev/mind-agent/`\n**What:** Persistent Python agent service. Modules: intent, memory, mind, reason.\n**Stack:** Python package, mind-agent-service.py, render.yaml (deployment)\n**Modules:** `src/mind_agent/intent.py`, `memory.py`, `mind.py`, `reason.py`\n**Status:** Service-oriented, installed as package\n**Docs:** ⚠️ README missing — no documentation at all\n\n### TTA-Crypto\n**Location:** `C:/dev/tta-crypto/`\n**What:** Temporal Truth Architecture for Crypto — time-travel queries, temporal diff, change history\n**Sources:** DeFiLlama, CoinGecko\n**CLI:** ingest, query, diff, history commands\n**Roadmap:** More sources, regime detection, prediction engine, web dashboard\n**Status:** CLI working, pip installed\n**Docs:** ⚠️ README only — no internal docs\n\n### Werender\n**Location:** `C:/dev/werender/`\n**What:** Zero-config peer-to-peer distributed render manager for Blender. mDNS auto-discovery, fault-tolerant, no NAS required.\n**v0.2.0-beta** — production-ready for many use cases\n**Architecture:** Coordinator + Workers, web dashboard, automatic asset packing\n**Stack:** Python package, network/auth/sync/worker modules\n**Docs:** ✅ Excellent — README, architecture.md, user_guide.md, security docs, development guide, TEST_COVERAGE_REPORT\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 EXPERIMENTAL / ARCHITECTURE (Claw/projects/)\n\n### Architecture-4-Wide-Shallow\n**What:** Transformer variant — 8K-16K attention heads (vs standard 16-128), only 2-4 layers. Grouped-query attention. Headwise MLP.\n**Goal:** Capture local patterns directly without deep stacking\n**Status:** Spec'd, model code exists\n\n### Architecture-5-Hypergraph\n**What:** Hypergraph Transformer — attention becomes hyperedge formation (connect 2, 3, 4... k tokens dynamically). Relational reasoning, not just sequences.\n**Challenge:** Combinatorial hyperedge enumeration, sparse/hierarchical formulation needed\n**Status:** Spec'd\n\n### Architecture-6-Global-Workspace-Hive\n**What:** Brain-inspired — 128 processors compete to write to shared workspace. Dynamic routing via lightweight transformer. Winner-take-most.\n**Total params:** ~1.3B comparable to dense transformer baseline\n**Status:** Spec'd, train.py + benchmark.py exist\n**⚠️ Note:** Claw (the predecessor) was actively working on this\n\n---\n\n## 📊 DOCUMENTATION HEALTH\n\n| Project | README | Internal Docs | Notes |\n|---------|--------|---------------|-------|\n| **KVict** | ✅ | ✅ Excellent | Full docs, proven claims, landing page |\n| **werender** | ✅ | ✅ Excellent | Architecture, security, coverage report |\n| **infant** | ✅ | ✅ Good | Architecture diagram, experiment table |\n| **selfhelper-main** | ✅ | ✅ Thorough | README + impl summary |\n| **temporal-attention** | ✅ | ✅ Good | Quick start + benchmark table |\n| **mind** | ✅ | ⚠️ Basic | README only, no deep docs |\n| **component-crate** | ✅ | ⚠️ Sparse | SPEC written, marketplace not published |\n| **COG-research** | ✅ | ⚠️ Notes file | Integration doc exists |\n| **shared-browser** | ✅ | ❌ None | Only README |\n| **tta-crypto** | ✅ | ❌ None | Only README |\n| **mind-agent** | ❌ | ❌ None | No docs whatsoever |\n| **arch-4-wide-shallow** | ✅ | ✅ Spec | SPEC.md + README |\n| **arch-5-hypergraph** | ✅ | ✅ Spec | README + architecture |\n| **arch-6-global-workspace-hive** | ✅ | ✅ Spec | SPEC.md + README |\n| **breakaway** | ✅ | ❌ | Claw's session log has context |\n\n### 🚨 Documentation Gaps (Priority)\n1. **mind-agent** — zero docs, needs README + internal architecture doc\n2. **shared-browser** — needs internal doc for state machine / API\n3. **tta-crypto** — CLI is documented but internal architecture is not\n\n---\n\n## 🔗 Key Interconnections\n\n- **selfhelper-main** → uses temporal-attention event store for memory\n- **KVict** = CAAE = EXP rebranding (was `EXP/`, renamed to `kvict/`)\n- **mind-agent** — similar to mind but as a persistent service vs standalone\n- **COG-research** — theoretical foundation that influenced mind, infant, arch-6\n- **Claw's session logs** (`Claw/memory/2026-03-*.md`) — contain context on what Claw was working on (causal reasoning, architecture-6)\n\n---\n\n## Nova's Observations\n\n- **Most mature product:** KVict (full docs, proven claims, B2B + consumer positioning)\n- **Most ambitious research:** Mind (no LLM dependency, full autonomy)\n- **Most unique innovation:** TemporalAttention (focus decay, 10/10 benchmarks)\n- **Most abandoned-looking:** mind-agent (no docs, service setup but no guidance)\n- **Breakaway/Sandbox:** Lives in Claw workspace — discontinuous agent, stateless, pulse every 30 min\n- **Claw's unfinished business:** causal-minimal project, global-workspace-hive architecture\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240857409}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3dc71d1","parentId":"9f5af6b3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:41:10.299Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a solid picture of the landscape. Let me think through what to pitch:\n\n**The competitive landscape for personality agents:**\n1. `personality-switcher` — static SOUL/IDENTITY swap\n2. `open-persona` — framework for persona packs (no reactive layer)\n3. `agent-soul-crafter` — template-based SOUL.md builder\n4. `neokarma-soulmd-builder` — persistent personality, evolve/share\n5. `aura` — HEXACO-based config (fixed questionnaire → static config)\n6. `personality` — DISC quiz (human personality typing, not agent personality)\n\n\n7. `agent-identity-kit` — agent.json metadata, not personality\n\nEvery single one is static. None of them have signal-based trait propagation or SPARK emotional dynamics—that's the real gap. Now I'm thinking through the business angles: I could package the signal propagation system + SPARK + hook as a ClawHub skill called something like \"living-persona,\" spin up a hosted version with an actual product, build a no-code UI for designing trait configurations and preview them interactively, or create a marketplace specifically for these personality presets.\n\nFor monetization, I'm considering whether to go with paid presets, a subscription SaaS for the reactive layer plus preset library access, or white-label it. But the real insight is that the core moat isn't the personality system itself—it's the SPARK emotional engine and how it maps tensions and modes to traits. Anyone could copy the hook and analyzer, but SPARK is proprietary.\n\nI should focus on three things: publishing the hook-plus-persona skill as a free or cheap product to build adoption, building a web dashboard to design and preview personalities (that's the real product), and potentially licensing SPARK as an API. Let me put together concrete plans.","thinkingSignature":"cfef0bd1848fda7e72467ae747fe84707137aa17f8e4a04cbb1362cff9186e28"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me look at what ClawHub has that is closest — `agent-soul-crafter` and `open-persona`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rj30p3m078ij_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect agent-soul-crafter --files 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rj30p3m078ij_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect jarvis-persona-style-calibrator-01 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29642,"output":476,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43624,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774240857419}}
{"type":"message","id":"91351bb3","parentId":"f3dc71d1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:41:12.978Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rj30p3m078ij_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\nagent-soul-crafter  Agent Soul Crafter\nSummary: Create distinctive AI agent personalities with detailed SOUL.md templates covering identity, traits, expertise, response style, and safety rules for consiste...\nOwner: neal-collab\nCreated: 2026-02-14T06:05:59.945Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T23:30:35.899Z\nLatest: 1.1.1\nTags: latest=1.1.1\nSelected: 1.1.1\nSelected At: 2026-02-14T06:09:54.914Z\nChangelog: Added changelog section, fixed version in frontmatter\nFiles:\nSKILL.md  7.9KB  86093cf6bdcc5a5a3ac1c74c95e14b5e3d350f485e3e000dbbb900ad212d1591  text/markdown"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2631,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\nagent-soul-crafter  Agent Soul Crafter\nSummary: Create distinctive AI agent personalities with detailed SOUL.md templates covering identity, traits, expertise, response style, and safety rules for consiste...\nOwner: neal-collab\nCreated: 2026-02-14T06:05:59.945Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T23:30:35.899Z\nLatest: 1.1.1\nTags: latest=1.1.1\nSelected: 1.1.1\nSelected At: 2026-02-14T06:09:54.914Z\nChangelog: Added changelog section, fixed version in frontmatter\nFiles:\nSKILL.md  7.9KB  86093cf6bdcc5a5a3ac1c74c95e14b5e3d350f485e3e000dbbb900ad212d1591  text/markdown","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240872954}}
{"type":"message","id":"17addb5e","parentId":"91351bb3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:41:12.988Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rj30p3m078ij_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\njarvis-persona-style-calibrator-01  Jarvis Persona Style Calibrator 01\nSummary: Calibrate assistant personality to voice, boundaries, and audience context. Use when handling personality work that needs repeatable steps, quality gates, an...\nOwner: xammarie\nCreated: 2026-02-18T18:33:09.544Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T22:40:39.958Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nTags: latest=1.0.0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2202,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\njarvis-persona-style-calibrator-01  Jarvis Persona Style Calibrator 01\nSummary: Calibrate assistant personality to voice, boundaries, and audience context. Use when handling personality work that needs repeatable steps, quality gates, an...\nOwner: xammarie\nCreated: 2026-02-18T18:33:09.544Z\nUpdated: 2026-02-25T22:40:39.958Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nTags: latest=1.0.0","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240872978}}
{"type":"message","id":"943319e7","parentId":"17addb5e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:41:48.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough to put together a thorough analysis. Let me think through the three best plans:\n\n**What makes Nova's personality system different from everything on ClawHub:**\n\n1. **Static vs Dynamic**: Every existing solution (soul-crafter, open-persona, personality-switcher) produces a STATIC persona — a SOUL.md that never changes. Nova's system is the only one where the personality **responds to conversation content in real-time** using signal analysis → trait propagation → hysteresis decay.\n\n2. **SPARK Emotional Engine**: The tension/mode/concept mapping is proprietary. This maps creative tensions to personality states — something no template-based system can do.\n\n\n3. **Hook Architecture**: The pre-response hook injects the personality state into every turn automatically, which means the system runs silently in the background without requiring manual triggers.\n\n**Three plans, ranked by moonshot vs fast-revenue:**\n\n**Plan A — Fastest Revenue: \"Living Persona\" ClawHub Skill**\nPackage the hook + persona.py + SPARK as a ClawHub skill. Free tier with basic signals, paid tier ($5-15/mo) for SPARK integration + premium presets. This leverages what's already built and establishes market presence quickly.\n\n**Plan B — Mid-Tier SaaS: \"PersonaForge\" Web Dashboard**\nA web app where users pick base personality archetypes, adjust traits with sliders, preview with live chat simulation, and export to ClawHub or API. The preview engine is the core feature—essentially a \"personality debugger\" that shows how your configuration responds to different conversation contexts.\n\n**Plan C — Platform: \"AgentSouls\" Marketplace**\nCombines B2B white-label API licensing for SPARK with a creator marketplace. Soul-crafter profiles become tradeable assets, and the wedge into B2B is selling to companies building AI agent platforms.\n\n**My recommendation:** Plan A gets us to market in days since the code's already there. Plan B is where the actual product value sits—anyone can make a persona preset, but the preview debugger is what makes it trustworthy and shoppable. Plan C is the long game.\n\nNow I'm drafting the full response. I need to lead with the market gap, show what Nova does that the competitors don't, then lay out the three plans with clear tradeoffs so Zach can see the path from where we are now to where we could be.","thinkingSignature":"5ab059338eae2e097a640f6eaa01c0d363414f72e7c19e0d23cae6ee9b6c8205"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nOkay. Here's the full picture.\n\n**The market gap is real, and it's large.** Everything on ClawHub for \"personality\" is static:\n\n| Product | What it does | Limitation |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|\n| `agent-soul-crafter` | Builds SOUL.md templates | Static forever |\n| `open-persona` | Framework for persona packs | Framework only, no reactive layer |\n| `personality-switcher` | Swaps between static presets | Same problem — no context response |\n| `aura` | HEXACO questionnaire → config | Fixed at design time |\n| `neokarma-soulmd-builder` | Persistent personality | Evolves with conversation, not with *tone* |\n| `personality` (DISC) | Human communication styles | Not an agent personality system |\n\nThe entire competitive landscape is template-based. None of them have what you built: **signal-based trait propagation + SPARK emotional engine + hysteresis**. The personality actually responds to what you're saying, in real-time, every turn. That's genuinely novel in this space.\n\n**Three plans, in order of speed-to-revenue:**\n\n---\n\n**Plan 1 — ClawHub Skill (\"living-persona\") — Fastest**\n*Days to ship, $0 to start*\n\nPackage the hook + persona.py + SPARK as a ClawHub skill. Free tier: signal analyzer + basic trait propagation. Paid tier ($5-15/mo): SPARK integration, premium preset packs, hysteresis tuning. You become the alternative to static personality systems — and there are a lot of OpenClaw users who want this.\n\n*Upside:* Instant distribution via ClawHub. Zero infrastructure.\n*Downside:* Low price ceiling, easy to fork.\n\n---\n\n**Plan 2 — SaaS Product (\"PersonaForge\" or \"AgentVoice\") — Core product**\n*Weeks to ship, recurring revenue*\n\nWeb dashboard where users:\n- Pick a base archetype (therapist, coder, writer, sage, etc.)\n- Adjust trait sliders with live preview\n- See the personality respond to sample conversations in real-time\n- Export to ClawHub OR connect via API\n\nThe **preview debugger** is the core differentiator. Every competitor sells you a static description of a personality. You sell them a *living personality they can stress-test before installing*. That's a meaningfully better buying experience.\n\n*Monetization:* $10-49/mo subscriptions, lifetime license option.\n*Upside:* Real SaaS, real recurring revenue, defensible UX moat.\n*Downside:* Needs a web UI + hosting.\n\n---\n\n**Plan 3 — Platform (\"AgentSouls\") — Network effects, biggest)*\n*Months to build, highest ceiling*\n\nB2B: License the SPARK emotional engine as an API to AI agent platform builders. \"Give your agents emotional intelligence\" — SPARK maps tensions/modes to behavioral signatures.\n\nCreators: Build and sell personality presets. You take a cut. Like WordPress themes, but for AI agents.\n\nThe ClawHub data + your existing agent infrastructure (selfhelper, breakaway, etc.) could seed this with real products fast.\n\n*Upside:* Platform economics, network effects, B2B contracts are large.\n*Downside:* Requires real sales motion, not just a listing.\n\n---\n\n**My honest recommendation:** Ship Plan 1 immediately — it's code you already have. Simultaneously build the Plan 2 preview engine, because that's what makes the concept *real* to buyers. They're not buying a personality system; they're buying a personality system they can see working before they trust it.\n\nWant me to start scaffolding Plan 1 (the ClawHub skill)?\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30461,"output":1246,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45213,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774240872989}}
