{"type":"message","id":"add3f35e","parentId":"8ab2d480","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:02:17.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the skill isn't on ClawHub yet (obviously). The package needs to be published. I need Zach's ClawHub login token to do this.Let me tell Zach what's done and what he needs to do to publish.","thinkingSignature":"e48a96b9fccb38df63c70bf433918e478d6c4cd6b3efe0994a103fec4832737f"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nIt's built, installed, and tested. Here's what's live:\n\n**Hook installed:** `living-persona` is in `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\hooks\\living-persona\\` and enabled.\n\n**Tested and working:**\n- Incoming: *\"frustrated with this python code...\"*  \n- Output: `[Voice directive] Active traits: candid, direct.` — proper structural injection\n\n**Files:**\n```\nliving-persona/\n├── SKILL.md           — skill description + usage\n├── HOOK.md            — hook documentation\n├── hook.json          — config (structural mode, hysteresis tuned)\n├── handler.ts         — the full personality engine (JS, runs in gateway process)\n├── references/\n│   ├── presets.md     — 7 presets: nova, cynic, sage, coach, ghost, hacker, romantic\n│   └── setup.md       — installation guide\n└── scripts/\n    └── reset_persona.py — reset trait state on /new\n```\n\n**To publish to ClawHub** — I need your login token:\n```bash\nclawhub login --token <your-token>\n```\nThen I can run `clawhub publish ./living-persona`. After that it's live on the marketplace.\n\n**Also:** the SPARK integration isn't wired into the TypeScript handler yet — the Python version has it, the JS port doesn't (no Python interpreter in the gateway process). That's the last piece if you want SPARK emotional engine in the structural layer too.\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48148,"output":358,"cacheRead":13506,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62012,"cost":{"input":0,"out